ZH: 素养包括人文素养和科学素养。
EN: Cultivation includes humanistic cultivation and scientific cultivation.

ZH: 学校很重视学生的素养培养。
EN: The school pays a lot of attention to the cultivation of students' character.

ZH: 思想道德的素养是一个人的重要标志。
EN: The moral and ideological cultivation is an important symbol of a person.

ZH: 素养的提高需要长期的积累和磨砺。
EN: Improving character requires long-term accumulation and honing.

ZH: 他出身于知识家庭，有很好的人文素养。
EN: He comes from an intellectual family and has a good humanistic cultivation.

ZH: 年轻人应该注重自身的素养提高。
EN: Young people should pay attention to improving their own cultivation.

ZH: 这个社会需要更多具有高素养的人才。
EN: This society needs more talented people with high cultivation.

ZH: 他的身上充满了传统中华文化的素养。
EN: His body is full of the cultivation of traditional Chinese culture.

ZH: 素养的形成离不开日常生活的熏陶。
EN: The formation of character cannot be separated from the influence of daily life.

ZH: 这本书不仅讲述了知识，还培养了读者的素养。
EN: This book not only teaches knowledge, but also cultivates the character of the readers.

ZH: 一个人的素养直接关系到他的终身事业。
EN: A person's character is directly related to his lifelong career.

ZH: 素养不仅仅是学习的问题，还包含了很多方面。
EN: Character is not just a matter of study, but also includes many aspects.

ZH: 小说让读者获得了人文素养的提升。
EN: Novels allow readers to improve their humanistic cultivation.

ZH: 素养的不断提高需要不断地自我反省。
EN: Improving character requires constant self-reflection.

ZH: 素养不但需要掌握知识，更需要注重道德修养。
EN: Character requires not only mastering knowledge, but also paying attention to moral cultivation.

ZH: 健康的体魄是素养的重要组成部分。
EN: A healthy body is an important part of character.

ZH: 素养和学识是人的两大基本素质。
EN: Cultivation and knowledge are the two basic qualities of a person.

ZH: 他在日常生活中展现了高尚的品德素养。
EN: He demonstrates noble moral cultivation in daily life.

ZH: 学校要培养学生的综合素养。
EN: Schools should cultivate students' comprehensive qualities.
